Environmental Waste Controls Seeks Admission to London’s AIM, Fundraising

-- B y   R a n d a l l   H a c k l e y
-- 
2011-05-02T10:18:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-02/environmental-waste-controls-seeks-admission-to-london-s-aim-fundraising.html
Environmental Waste Controls Plc, a
U.K. waste management services provider, said today that it
intends to seek admission to  London ’s AIM market and raise as
much as 4 million pounds ($6.7 million) to fund its growth.  The Liverpool-based company, which employs about 370
workers in the household waste recycling and commercial waste
management divisions, reported sales in the fiscal year that
ended last August of 24 million pounds.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Hackley in Zurich at 
